        public Alu(Tape tapeIn,
           Tape tapeOut,
           ProgramMemory programMemory,
           DataMemory dataMemory,
           java.util.ArrayList<Tag> tagList,
           java.lang.Boolean debug)
        Constructs a new Alu given all the specified components.
        Parameters:
        tapeIn - input tape.
        tapeOut - output tape.
        programMemory - program memory used by the ALU.
        dataMemory - data memory used by the ALU.
        tagList - contains all the tags of the current program.
        debug - specifies the debug mode if it's true, otherwise debug mode will be disabled.
